04473nam a22006735i 9789633865309DE-B159720220729113935.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220729t20222000hu     fo  d z      eng d  a97896338653097 a10.1515/97896338653092doi  a(DE-B1597)633379  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  ahucHU 7aPOL0110002bisacsh1 aBalmaceda, Margarita M., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aOn The Edge :bUkrainian - Central European - Russian Security Triangle /cMargarita M. Balmaceda. 1aBudapest ;aNew York : bCentral European University Press, c[2022] 4c©2000  a1 online resource (280 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tList of Contributors -- tList of Tables -- tPreface and Acknowledgements -- t1. Ukraine, Central Europe, and Russia in a New International Environment -- t2. The Warsaw-Kyiv-Moscow Security Triangle -- t3. The Slovak-Ukrainian-Russian Security Triangle -- t4. The Hungarian-Ukrainian- Russian Triangle: Not Like Rubik's Cube -- t5. Economic Relations and the Ukrainian-Central European- Russian Triangle -- t6. The Triangle with Five Sides: Patterns of Relations between Poland, Slovakia, Hungary, Ukraine, and Russia -- t7. The Ukrainian-Central European Borderland after NATO Expansion: Wall, Fortress, or Open Door? -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aA new globally significant relationship arising after the break-up of the Soviet Union is the main topic of this unparalleled volume – the geopolitical link between Russia, Ukraine and the three bordering ‘Central European’ states, Hungary, Poland and Slovakia. On the Edge is a path-breaking analysis of this triangular relationship with an in-depth focus on economic, political and, more importantly, security issues. The expansion of NATO up to Ukraine’s borders is likely to leave Ukraine in a delicate position vis-à-vis Russia. On the Edge addresses key questions, such as: how are events in Ukraine affecting the security calculations of the Central European states; Central European relations with Russia and NATO; and relations among Central European states themselves? The volume examines what Central European states can do to solidify Ukraine’s independence and help it avoid international isolation. On the Edge gives a Central European perspective on all these issues and suggests concrete forms of co-operation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh  aNational Security, International relations, Late 20th century.  aNorth Atlantic Treaty Organization.1 aBalmaceda, Margarita M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalka, Marek, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuleba, Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPóti, László, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCentral European University Press eBook-Package 2013-1998z978311078055040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978963386530940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789633865309423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789633865309/original  a978-3-11-078055-0  Central European University Press eBook-Package 2013-1998c1998d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK